      <gmd:abstract>
        <gco:CharacterString>
          The EMO database compiles Eocene marine ostracode records from multiple sources including the Paleobiology Database (PBDB), World Register of Marine Species (WoRMS), published literature, and original datasets. The database provides standardized taxonomic, spatial, and temporal information to support paleoecological and macroevolutionary analyses.
        </gco:CharacterString>
      </gmd:abstract>

